            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Sad Occurrence</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Tells of the sad death of a sentinel from the Georgia Regiment named
                    Meyers. He was shot by another soldier in his regiment while the troops were
                    camped at Shaw's Fork near Staunton.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Skirmish at Phillippi</head>
                <origin>Richmond Enquirer</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Hanger</ln>
                        <fn>James</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Reports that James Hanger of Augusta was not killed at Phillippi, as
                    previously reported. He was wounded and had his leg amputated below the knee.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>The Northwest</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Gen. R.S. Garnett has taken command of Confederate forces in northwestern
                    Virginia. The Vindicator believes that the people in that part of the state can
                    be brought back into the Confederacy.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>4</column>
                <head/>
                <origin>Richmond Enquirer</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>A letter in the Enquirer states that "The Vandal horde that has invaded the
                    soil of Virginia, is engaged in plundering farms, and farm houses, killing
                    cattle, sheep, hogs &amp;c., and in many instances tearing down houses for
                    fuel."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>4</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
